Text.Value: But if he is not, he has a chance to do some good today. To set right a little of the pain he has caused in his miserable existence.
What's she saying?
My thanks. I only pray his anger at his old master burns as brightly as ours.
Perhaps he will not. Perhaps he is the monster we believe him to be.
And if it's too late to save your children?
Forgive me. I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].
The same Astarion who killed our kin Gandrel and left him to rot in a hag's swamp.
But alas, taking our revenge on him would likely doom us all.
Prayers for the fallen. We are burning their belongings so they may fight on in the afterlife.
*You recognise the words - Gur funeral rites. To hear them is rare: the Gur monster hunters are as formidable as they are secretive.*
We were not able to save our children, but perhaps one of his own - your Astarion - could enter safely, destroy Cazador, and save them?
I thought I knew the faces of all your friends, Gandrel, but this one is new to me.
What can you tell me about Cazador's lair?
What's left of my tribe is wounded and broken - we cannot stand against him to save our children. But perhaps the slayer of Ketheric could?
If you will not help us, we do not need you here.
I'll see what can be done.
I admit, I would have relished it. But his death would not have served us well.
Baldur's Gate is haunted by many things, but one of its most insidious is the vampire Cazador.
And this is the one I spoke of, my lady - the stranger I met while hunting the spawn.
Speak the traditional Rashemi blessing for fallen warriors.
Slay the vampire, claim his head, and free our children. Please.
Some rescue...
The same Astarion that came in the night with his wretched siblings and stole away my tribe's children.
We tried to save them, but his palace was too well defended.
Well, here I am. What are you going to do about it?
Astarion isn't responsible for the crimes Cazador forced him to commit.
They could not.
I take no pride in killing nor trophies from it. Sometimes it simply must be done.
And? What's Ketheric to you?
I do not know if showing your face here is brave or stupid, given the company you keep.
Should I... go?
And why in the hells would Astarion take you up on this?
The children of my tribe were taken from us. Stolen in the night and brought to Cazador's palace by your friend and his siblings.
I'll chop him into so many bits you won't know he was a vampire.
Enlighten me.
Oh yes, I know you hid him from me. But this is not the moment to discuss it. This is about the dead, not the undead.
I'm not interested.
I didn't know this was a funeral. I'm sorry for your loss.
No, that shame is mine alone.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Approaching the players from the direction of the campfire
EditorData.NodeContext: Approaching the players from the direction of the campfire

Text.Value: I will say no more. It is not my tale to tell.
Please, will you take him now? He's so annoying.
Rech té i hathran roost.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looking onto a pyre, where a variety of possessions are being burned - armour and broken weapons, as well as clothing,
EditorData.SFXTags: [WI] tossing of armors, burning audio support, pyre sfx.
EditorData.VFXTags: [WI] potentially pyre/fire/ember vfx, or we could just also use existing game object if its available

Text.Value: But perhaps I can interest you in claiming another prize?
Two fine trophies. Perhaps I can interest you in a third?
His life may, however.
Maybe Gandrel didn't leave him much choice.
You'll forgive the person who stole your children?
This is the one who hid the spawn from you?
Yes, I killed Ketheric.
Yeah, I'm definitely not doing that.
A noble goal. I will not ask you to deviate from it, but know that this city holds other dangers too.
Our tribe left camp on a rescue mission. Only Ulma and those you see here returned.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Gwen Lee] Please reuse HUM_M_Rig_DFLT_CINE_NodHead_Yes_StandL_03 for his nod.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nodding to Ulma, the camp matriach, standing in front of him. She's by a funeral pyre, leading prayers, so a small distance away

Text.Value: *She's speaking the language of the Gur people, one influenced by ancient Rashemi tongues. She's praying for the fallen of her tribe as their possessions are burned.*
Yes, we are familiar with Astarion.
My thanks. We grieve those who left us, but celebrate them too. They died well.
May the gods keep you and damn your enemies.
I'm sorry for your loss, but I have my own fight.
The wretched undead.
Welcome, friend. You find us on a solemn day.
If you have taken one undead trophy, perhaps I can interest you in another?
Lady, I have no idea who you are.
Why, what happened?
And if whispered tales can be believed, he was defeated by one looking much like you.
Alas, now he is more valuable with you.
You have travelled with Astarion, a spawn sired and raised by the vampire Cazador.
Perhaps. What do you have in mind?
*You've clearly walked into some kind of ceremony, but it's nothing that you recognise.*
A risk was taken. Unfortunately, it led to disaster.
Together you could save those stolen from us and help your companion destroy his old master. We would all be free.
Oh, they're nothing compared to my sins.
A vampire spawn is doubly cursed - first to be a slave, but still to be a monster. He is not so innocent.
They killed not only that fen's hag, but also the undying General Thorm, if the rumours are true.
In the city lives Cazador Szarr, a powerful man - a respected man. A man known to host lavish, hedonistic banquets in his palace.
I know the Gur people have a history with a vampire spawn named Astarion.
No, but he may be useful.
A pity. You had a chance to cleanse his hands of some blood.
The head of the shadow-cursed warlord is an impressive trophy. I am wondering if I could tempt you with another.
As we all hope to.
A fine trophy. Perhaps you would like to claim another?
I thought you were going to kill him!
He won't make a deal with you and neither will I.
Cazador must be destroyed. For the safety of the city, and to make sure no one else must feel our pain.
But behind the façade, there is a monster. A vampire who has made Baldur's Gate a feeding ground and his palace an abattoir.
*You recognise the funeral rites of the Gur people - famed monster hunters. She's burning the possessions of those who have fallen.*
I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].
Crude, but not untrue. And who is this, Gandrel?
Gandrel was doing his duty, trying to save our tribe's future.
Can it be true? Perhaps you are more powerful than I give you credit for.
What killed them?
A time like what, exactly?

EditorData.stateContext: Ulma is standing in front of a burning pyre, arms raised, reciting funeral rites for fallen soldiers

Text.Value: The slayer of Ketheric Thorm? Well, these are strange times indeed.
I'll do whatever I can.
Ah... him.
The spawn can infiltrate Cazador's palace in a way we never could. And he could take you with him.
Only because it is necessary.
I did not. He slipped by me, although how I do not know.
They took our children. Every last one - our whole future.
*You recognise the language of the Gur people, sprinkled with words from ancient Rashemi tongues, but you cannot follow what's being said.*
I have other battles to fight.
It may be watched, but you will not walk into the slaughter that we did.
There is doom in the air these days, but welcome news too. Word has reached me that the undying Ketheric Thorm is destroyed.
His crimes against my people are legion. His name is cursed on our lips.
And they went on to kill the undying General Thorm, if the rumours are true.
Very well, but I pray you do not save yourself from one terror only to fall to the next.
This may be true, but your sins have not been visited upon us. Unlike your campmate Astarion.
Did they save whoever they set out to rescue?
But even so, there are others whose crimes are greater.
We await an audience with your spawn.
No? A pity - the head of the shadow-cursed warlord would have made a fine trophy.
And? What if he was?

EditorData.stateContext: Ulma standing, talking to players in normal positioning

Text.Value: Im orak ne tay. Krasin ne trah!

EditorData.NodeContext: IM or-AK nay tay. KRAS-in nay TRAH

Text.Value: I don't travel with Astarion anymore. He's long gone.
For years, his foul spawn have stolen away innocents at night, whisking them back to his palace. Recently, they struck our camp.
I would make peace with your Astarion. I would forgive him his sins if we can reach an accord.
The main entrance is blockaded, but there is another way. Near the park, you will find a broken tower, mid-repair. Climb the scaffolding and you can enter his palace.
I see you have studied our tongue, friend. You are quite correct - we underestimated an enemy.
Less than I'd like. We made it to the main hall before his slaves attacked.
But no matter - he is gone and the past is done. I wish to discuss the future.
My friend from the hag swamp? You are a bright light on a dark day.
Gandrel was just telling me how you got your arse kicked.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Gwen Lee] HUM_F_Rig_SCENE_DEN_DruidServant_Prayer_PraySolo_Plyr for the start, then HUM_F_Rig_DFLT_CINE_Walk_01, and end with HUM_F_Rig_DFLT_CINE_Walk_ToStandL_01.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ulma pauses for a moment, staring at the fire in contemplation before she turns and walks over to the player.

Text.Value: Prayers for the fallen - we are burning their belongings so they may fight on in the next life. Battling monsters like your pale friend, perhaps.
I'm sorry for your loss.
So... did you ever find that vampire spawn?
We underestimated an enemy. Much like I underestimated you and your vampiric companion.
If you do this, our entire tribe will be in your debt. On our honour, it will be repaid.
You are a roach upon the world. It will be a pleasure to stamp you out.
We suspect he holds his victims somewhere below his mansion. And we fear our missing children are among them.
We underestimated an enemy.
All right, I'll talk to Astarion.
I pledge your dead my respects - your quarry must have been impressive.
I'm already hunting another monster.
I admit, I am surprised. I thought your pale companion would kill for a chance to face his old master.
But I will enjoy ridding this world of one more monster.
There is no need - all are welcome to remember the fallen.
Then we will settle for blood.
I thought perhaps we could talk, but no. There is no common ground here.
I'm just a traveller - I've never heard of this 'Ketheric', let alone killed him.
How am I meant to get in if this palace is so well guarded?
I am Ulma, leader of what remains of my tribe. Your vampiric friend stole away our children, and we have lost many trying to save them.
What kind of accord?
In Astarion's defence, the look on Gandrel's face as he died was priceless.
You'll have to be more specific - I know some interesting people.
Do you even know the sins of the one you travel with? The one you protect?
We tried to save them and paid a heavy price. But perhaps the slayer of Ketheric could succeed where we failed?
It is a solemn task - one this city forces us to undertake time and again.
You said those rites beautifully - I'm sorry for your loss.
I did not. Although I suspect you knew that much already.
Thank you, kin. You honour our fallen in these dark times.
We would not normally tolerate outsiders at a time like this.
Nothing, for these are not normal times.
Those who have left us will be celebrated, not mourned. They died well, after all.
Frey vald isk durovna. Frey vald isk ablast.

EditorData.NodeContext: FREY vald isk dur-OF-nah. FREY vald isk ab-LAST

Text.Value: Do not stand here and wait - Cazador must be destroyed!
A friend met on the road, my lady. I told you of the stranger in the swamp?
You find us honouring our dead. Celebrating those who fell in battle trying to save our tribe.
They tore us to pieces - vampire spawn and werewolves - I have never seen a vampire's lair so heavily guarded.
We are monster hunters all - our purpose is to kill beasts like these. But in our haste to save our little ones, we were rash. We charged straight into an ambush.

Synopsis:
Ulma, the leader of Gur Tribe, talks to the player while Astarion is not around. If Gandrel (Gur Hunter from Act 1) is alive, also present. Ulma speaks in an accented lilt - English is not her first language.
